---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

// Turnstile site key comes from a public env var at build. With a key, the
// form is live: real widget, enabled submit. Without one, the form stays in
// its pre-launch placeholder state. We never ship a tracking script here;
// Turnstile is a bot check, not analytics.
const turnstileSiteKey = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY ?? "";
const formLive = Boolean(turnstileSiteKey);
---

<Base
  title="Tell your story"
  description="Share what happened with a carrier device promotion, in your own words. You choose to send it. A person reviews it before anything is published."
>
  <div class="wrap prose" data-pagefind-body>
    <h1>Tell your story</h1>

    {
      !formLive && (
        <div class="notice">
          <p>
            <strong>Submissions open soon.</strong> This form is not live yet.
            The consent notice and the fields below are the real ones. Once
            submissions open, the form posts to a protected endpoint and a
            person reviews every story.
          </p>
        </div>
      )
    }
    <div class="notice" id="form-status" hidden>
      <p id="form-status-text"></p>
    </div>

    <h2>Read this before you submit</h2>
    <p>By submitting, you agree to this consent notice.</p>

    <div class="citation" aria-label="Submission consent">
      <p>
        <strong>What happens to my story.</strong> I am sending my story so it can
        help show a pattern. A person on the team reads it before anything is
        published. It is not posted automatically.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Who reads it.</strong> The team reads it during review. If facts
        need checking, a reviewer may look at it more closely.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>What gets removed before it is shown.</strong> Before my story is
        displayed, the team scrubs out anything that identifies me. That includes
        my name, account numbers, my exact address, and other identifying
        details. If a location is shown, it is only at the city, state, or zip
        level. Never my exact address.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Contact and verification.</strong> If I choose to give contact
        info, the team may contact me to check facts. Giving contact info is
        optional. My contact info is never displayed.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Withdrawing my story.</strong> I can withdraw my story at any
        time. If I ask, the team takes it off the site. The team keeps an internal
        copy for its records, and that copy is never displayed or shared.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>No lawyer or agent relationship.</strong> Submitting my story does
        not make anyone here my lawyer or my agent. No one here represents me.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>My promise about the story.</strong> I confirm this story is mine.
        I confirm it is true to the best of my knowledge.
      </p>
      <p><strong>My age.</strong> I confirm I am at least 18 years old.</p>
      <p>
        The full text is on the
        <a href="/legal/submission-consent">submission consent</a> page.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>Your story</h2>
    <form action="/api/submit" method="post" novalidate>
      <div class="field">
        <label for="what-happened">What happened</label>
        <textarea
          id="what-happened"
          name="what_happened"
          required
          placeholder="Tell it in your own words. What were you promised, and what actually happened? Talk to text works fine."
        ></textarea>
        <p class="hint">Use your own words. Do not copy someone else's story.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="field">
        <label for="carrier">Carrier</label>
        <select id="carrier" name="carrier">
          <option value="">Choose one</option>
          <option value="att">AT&T</option>
          <option value="verizon">Verizon</option>
          <option value="tmobile">T-Mobile</option>
          <option value="other">Other</option>
        </select>
      </div>

      <div class="field">
        <label for="city">City</label>
        <input id="city" name="city" type="text" autocomplete="off" />
      </div>

      <div class="field">
        <label for="state">State</label>
        <input
          id="state"
          name="state"
          type="text"
          maxlength="2"
          placeholder="Two letters, like CA"
          autocomplete="off"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="field">
        <label for="zip">ZIP</label>
        <input
          id="zip"
          name="zip"
          type="text"
          inputmode="numeric"
          maxlength="5"
          autocomplete="off"
        />
        <p class="hint">
          Location is shown at city, state, or zip level only. Never your exact
          address.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="field">
        <label for="contact">Contact (optional)</label>
        <input id="contact" name="contact" type="text" autocomplete="off" />
        <p class="hint">
          Optional. Only used to check facts with you. Never displayed. Ever.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="field">
        <label for="agree">
          <input id="agree" name="agree" type="checkbox" style="width:auto;" />
          I have read the consent notice above and I agree to it.
        </label>
      </div>

      <div class="field">
        <p class="hint">Human check</p>
        {
          formLive ? (
            <div class="cf-turnstile" data-sitekey={turnstileSiteKey} />
          ) : (
            <div class="turnstile-placeholder">
              Cloudflare Turnstile appears here when submissions open. It
              checks that a real person is submitting. It is not a tracking
              cookie.
            </div>
          )
        }
      </div>

      {
        formLive ? (
          <button type="submit" class="btn">Submit my story</button>
        ) : (
          <button type="submit" class="btn" disabled aria-disabled="true">
            Submit (opens soon)
          </button>
        )
      }
      {
        !formLive && (
          <p class="hint">
            The submit button is off until submissions open. Nothing is sent.
          </p>
        )
      }
    </form>

    {formLive && <script is:inline async defer src="https://challenges.cloudflare.com/turnstile/v0/api.js"></script>}

    <script is:inline>
      // Show the outcome message the submit endpoint redirects back with.
      // Static site, so this tiny reader is the whole mechanism.
      (function () {
        var messages = {
          "human-check": "The human check did not pass. Please try again.",
          consent: "Please read and check the consent box before submitting.",
          "too-short": "Please tell us a bit more. A few sentences is plenty.",
          closed: "Submissions are not open yet. Nothing was sent.",
        };
        var status = new URLSearchParams(location.search).get("status");
        if (status && messages[status]) {
          var box = document.getElementById("form-status");
          var text = document.getElementById("form-status-text");
          if (box && text) {
            text.textContent = messages[status];
            box.hidden = false;
          }
        }
      })();
    </script>

    <h2>After a story is verified</h2>
    <p>
      Once a story is reviewed, scrubbed, and consented, it gets its own stable
      page with a share card. You can post your own story link back to wherever
      you first vented. That is an invitation, not a task. No reward, no counter,
      no badge for sharing.
    </p>
  </div>

  <style>
    .turnstile-placeholder {
      border: 2px dashed var(--border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 1rem;
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text-soft);
      max-width: var(--measure);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
    button[disabled] {
      opacity: 0.6;
      cursor: not-allowed;
    }
  </style>
</Base>
